China Forbes (born April 29, 1970) is an American singer and songwriter who has been the lead singer of the band Pink Martini since 1995.
After graduating in 1992, Forbes worked as an actress for several years, performing Off-Broadway in New York City.
After three years commuting from New York, she moved to Portland in 1998 to work full-time with the band.
Apart from her work with Pink Martini, she has released solo albums, including Love Handle (November 1995) and '78 (Heinz 2008) which includes her song "Hey Eugene" in its original version.
